==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Luddite
<hw>Lud"dite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of a number of
riotous persons in England, who for six years (1811-17) tried to prevent
the use of labor-saving machinery by breaking it, burning factories,
etc.; -- so called from <person>Ned <etsep>Lud</etsep></person>, a
half-witted man who some years previously had broken stocking
frames.</def> <rj><au>J. & H. Smith.</au> <au>H.
Martineau.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ludibrious</ent>⟦br⟧
